===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*men-|id=think}}
From {{inh|en|enm|minde}}, {{m|enm|munde|münde}}, {{m|enm|ȝemünde}}, from {{inh|en|ang|mynd}}, {{m|ang|ġemynd|t=memory, remembrance; memorial, record; act of commemoration; thought, purpose; consciousness, mind, intellect}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*mundiz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*gamundiz|t=memory, remembrance}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*méntis|t=thought}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*men-|t=to think}}. Cognate with {{cog|goh|gimunt|t=mind, memory}}, {{cog|da|minde|t=memory}}, {{cog|is|minni|t=memory, recall, recollection}}, {{cog|got|𐌼𐌿𐌽𐌳𐍃|t=memory, mind}}, {{cog|la|mēns|t=mind, reason}}, {{cog|sa|मनस्|tr=mánas}}, {{cog|grc|μένος}}, {{cog|sq|mënd|t=mind, reason}}. Related to {{cog|ang|myntan|t=to mean, intend, purpose, determine, resolve}}. More at {{l|en|mint#Etymology 3}}.

