#: {{ux|en|He was one of history’s greatest '''minds'''.}}
# Judgment, opinion, or view.
#: {{ux|en|He changed his '''mind''' after hearing the speech.}}
# Desire, inclination, or intention.
#: {{ux|en|She had a '''mind''' to go to Paris.}}
#: {{ux|en|I have [[half a mind]] to do it myself.}}
#: {{ux|en|I am of a '''mind''' to listen.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1859|author=Charles Dickens|title=A Tale of Two Cities|passage=Although Miss Pross, through her long association with a French family, might have known as much of their language as of her own, if she had had a mind, she had no '''mind''' in that direction {{...}} So her manner of marketing was to plump a noun-substantive at the head of a shopkeeper without any introduction in the nature of an article {{...}}}}
